The paper is about a domain-specific language for scientific visualization of multidimensional images, which involves tensor fields and differential operators. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Graphics (cs.GR), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Scientific Computing (cs.SC), Software Engineering (cs.SE), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. However, since the paper focuses on the compilation of the language to C, it is most likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category is also likely, as the paper mentions visualization algorithms. The Scientific Computing (cs.SC) sub-category is less likely, as the paper does not focus on numerical methods or simulations. The Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories are even less likely, as they are not directly related to the paper's topic.
